@page "/About"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>VGLog - About</PageTitle>

<h1>VGLog</h1>
<p>Your personal videogame journal — track, reflect, and own your gaming history.</p>

<hr />

<h2>What is it</h2>
<p>
    VGLog is a personal videogame tracking web application. I've built this app by scratch as a way to learn the back-end and front-end (even though i prefer the back-end part way more). In this app
    you can easily keep track of your log of games by adding the games to your profile and giving them a vote and your opinion.
</p>
<hr />

<h2>Features</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Dashboard: </strong>An easy way to check on your journey with basic stats.</li>
    <li><strong>Game Tracking: </strong>Log every game you've played, are playing, or plan to play. Set statuses, played hours and notes for each one of them.</li>
    <li><strong>Statistics: </strong>Visualize your gaming habits. See how many games you've finished, dropped, or have yet to start and many other statistics.</li>
    <li><strong>User Profile: </strong>A personal profile page that summarizes your gaming activity and showcases your collection.</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h2>Tech stack</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>ASP.NET Core: </strong>Backend framework powering the application server and API layer.</li>
    <li><strong>Blazor Server: </strong>Razor components for interactive UI with real-time server-side rendering.</li>
    <li><strong>Radzen: </strong>UI component library for polished, accessible interface elements.</li>
    <li><strong>Entity Framework: </strong>ORM for seamless database access and migrations.</li>
    <li><strong>Azure App Service: </strong>Cloud hosting with scalability and reliability built in.</li>
    <li><strong>GitHub Actions: </strong>Automated CI/CD pipeline for continuous integration and deployment.</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h2>The developer</h2>
<p>
    My name is Marco Attura and i'm a self-taught developer that started in August of 2024 that led me to follow a regional funded course for programming that i passed with a score of 30/30.
    VGLog is a personal side project, built out of a genuine love for both gaming and software development.
    It started as a way to learn and face difficulties that you can only face by creating something like this and turned into a full-stack project covering cloud deployment,
    CI/CD pipelines, and component-driven UI design.
</p>
